  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing safe and equitable access to quality and inclusive education in a protective environment for children affected by the conflict in Konduga, Gwoza and Madagali.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective: Children affected by conflict have safe and equitable access to quality, inclusive and protective education

To achieve the above project objective, Plan international foresees the following key activities:
Back to Learning campaigns and awareness raising
Temporary learning spaces and gender segregated latrines with hand washing facilities
Temporary seat facilities
Teaching and learning kits
Dignity kits for adolescent girls
Teacher training in pedagogy, classroom management, child protection and psychosocial support
System strengthening and community mobilisation through training of School-based Management Committees to restore, protect and support education
Temporary learning spaces for Early Childhood Development (that will also be used as Child Friendly Spaces in the afternoons)
ECD facilitator training
ECD facilitator incentives
Teaching and learning kits for ECD centres
Parenting sessions to support ECD centres and protect children from harm
Recreational kits

Target beneficiaries:
The proposed action will target 750 boys and girls aged 3-6 for early childhood development (ECD) and 10,000 boys and girls aged 6-17 for basic education. Both in and out of school children will be targeted through the project with an aim of increasing enrolment and retention, as well as school attendance. A further 1500 children will access recreational and play materials in the afternoons at the child friendly spaces (ECD learning centres will be used in the afternoons this function).

Plan international requests funding of 400,000 USD for a 9-month period for implementing education in emergencies. The requested fund will be used for creating access to education for conflict affected children, improve the quality of learning while providing a protective learning environment for children under the do no harm policy.

The project will target both host communities, IDPs and returnees in the 3 target local government areas of Konduga and Gwoza (in Borno state) and Madagali (in Adamawa state). Plan international currently has on-going projects in the selected local government areas and is co-leading a subchapter of the Education in Emergencies Working Group in Adamawa state.</narrative>
  </description>
